<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-09-17T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-09-17T13:00:00-05:00" n="162" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d162">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">651.113/109a: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Ambassador in France (<persName type="to">Edge</persName>)</hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-09-17T14:00:00-04:00">September 17, 1932—2
                                        p.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>327. The copper interests are anxious to obtain relief from the
                                discrimination in favor of Belgium. Has there been any recent
                                progress in this matter?</p>
                            <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_SHL1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>